{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_276d630d043545829584f53a","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t[<img width=250px src=https://www.ilamb.org/assets/images/RUBISCO1.png>](https://www.bgc-feedbacks.org/)\n2\t\n3\t# ILAMB - International Land Model Benchmarking\n4\t\n5\tThe python package designed to help confront earth system models with reference data products, and then present the results in a hierarchical set of webpages. Please see [ilamb.org](https://www.ilamb.org) where we have details about the datasets we use, the results we catalog, and the methods we employ.\n6\t\n7\t## v2.7.3 Release - January 2025\n8\t\n9\tThis update contains many bugfixes found while supporting papers and other model-data comparison work in the community. You may sense that the development of ILAMB has slowed down. Code development at *this* repository has slowed, but ILAMB continues to change. Many datasets are being added to our comparisons but that activity happens in a different repository (see [ILAMB-Data](https://github.com/rubisco-sfa/ILAMB-Data)). \n10\t\n11\tWe have also been developing a rewrite of the ILAMB software which leverages more modern analysis packages, in particular xarray. The new ILAMB version also is meant to address a shift in how scientists work. Originally ILAMB was envisioned as a replacement for diagnostics packages that modeling centers run. However in the past 10 years, it has become more common for scientists to run small analyses in notebooks as part of their model development process. This new version of ILAMB will find a balance between the operational diagnostic package and the ability to import functionality for creative uses. At the moment, we are developing this as a separate package we call [ilamb3](https://github.com/rubisco-sfa/ilamb3). Check it out along with its accompanying [documentation](https://ilamb3.readthedocs.io/en/latest/).\n12\t\n13\t## Funding\n14\t\n15\tThis research was performed for the *Reducing Uncertainties in\n16\tBiogeochemical Interactions through Synthesis and Computation*\n17\t(RUBISCO) Scientific Focus Area, which is sponsored by the Regional\n18\tand Global Climate Modeling (RGCM) Program in the Climate and\n19\tEnvironmental Sciences Division (CESD) of the Biological and\n20\tEnvironmental Research (BER) Program in the U.S. Department of Energy\n21\tOffice of Science.\n22\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8f03c8eb-29e8-40b3-9ecc-11dd41b1ad27","uuid":"b81c42ce-28a7-4a2b-ac69-929146224de8","timestamp":"2026-04-09T00:42:07.470Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.md","content":"[<img width=250px src=https://www.ilamb.org/assets/images/RUBISCO1.png>](https://www.bgc-feedbacks.org/)\n\n# ILAMB - International Land Model Benchmarking\n\nThe python package designed to help confront earth system models with reference data products, and then present the results in a hierarchical set of webpages. Please see [ilamb.org](https://www.ilamb.org) where we have details about the datasets we use, the results we catalog, and the methods we employ.\n\n## v2.7.3 Release - January 2025\n\nThis update contains many bugfixes found while supporting papers and other model-data comparison work in the community. You may sense that the development of ILAMB has slowed down. Code development at *this* repository has slowed, but ILAMB continues to change. Many datasets are being added to our comparisons but that activity happens in a different repository (see [ILAMB-Data](https://github.com/rubisco-sfa/ILAMB-Data)). \n\nWe have also been developing a rewrite of the ILAMB software which leverages more modern analysis packages, in particular xarray. The new ILAMB version also is meant to address a shift in how scientists work. Originally ILAMB was envisioned as a replacement for diagnostics packages that modeling centers run. However in the past 10 years, it has become more common for scientists to run small analyses in notebooks as part of their model development process. This new version of ILAMB will find a balance between the operational diagnostic package and the ability to import functionality for creative uses. At the moment, we are developing this as a separate package we call [ilamb3](https://github.com/rubisco-sfa/ilamb3). Check it out along with its accompanying [documentation](https://ilamb3.readthedocs.io/en/latest/).\n\n## Funding\n\nThis research was performed for the *Reducing Uncertainties in\nBiogeochemical Interactions through Synthesis and Computation*\n(RUBISCO) Scientific Focus Area, which is sponsored by the Regional\nand Global Climate Modeling (RGCM) Program in the Climate and\nEnvironmental Sciences Division (CESD) of the Biological and\nEnvironmental Research (BER) Program in the U.S. Department of Energy\nOffice of Science.\n","numLines":22,"startLine":1,"totalLines":22}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_f84af2c76660403d8c97a8a1","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t#!/usr/bin/env python\n2\timport os\n3\timport subprocess\n4\tfrom codecs import open\n5\t\n6\tfrom setuptools import setup\n7\t\n8\tVERSION = \"2.7.3\"\n9\t\n10\t\n11\tdef git_version():\n12\t    \"\"\"\n13\t    Return the sha1 of local git HEAD as a string.\n14\t    \"\"\"\n15\t\n16\t    def _minimal_ext_cmd(cmd):\n17\t        # construct minimal environment\n18\t        env = {}\n19\t        for k in [\"SYSTEMROOT\", \"PATH\", \"PYTHONPATH\"]:\n20\t            v = os.environ.get(k)\n21\t            if v is not None:\n22\t                env[k] = v\n23\t        # LANGUAGE is used on win32\n24\t        env[\"LANGUAGE\"] = \"C\"\n25\t        env[\"LANG\"] = \"C\"\n26\t        env[\"LC_ALL\"] = \"C\"\n27\t        out = subprocess.Popen(cmd, stdout=subprocess.PIPE, env=env).communicate()[0]\n28\t        return out\n29\t\n30\t    try:\n31\t        out = _minimal_ext_cmd([\"git\", \"rev-parse\", \"HEAD\"])\n32\t        git_revision = out.strip().decode(\"ascii\")\n33\t    except OSError:\n34\t        git_revision = \"unknown-git\"\n35\t    return git_revision[:7]\n36\t\n37\t\n38\tdef write_text(filename, text):\n39\t    try:\n40\t        with open(filename, \"w\") as a:\n41\t            a.write(text)\n42\t    except Exception as e:\n43\t        print(e)\n44\t\n45\t\n46\tdef write_version_py(filename=os.path.join(\"src/ILAMB\", \"generated_version.py\")):\n47\t    cnt = \"\"\"\n48\t# THIS FILE IS GENERATED FROM ILAMB SETUP.PY\n49\tshort_version = '%(version)s'\n50\tversion = '%(version)s'\n51\tgit_revision = '%(git_revision)s'\n52\tfull_version = '%(version)s (%%(git_revision)s)' %% {\n53\t    'git_revision': git_revision}\n54\trelease = %(isrelease)s\n55\tif not release:\n56\t    version = full_version\n57\t\"\"\"\n58\t    FULL_VERSION = VERSION\n59\t    if os.path.isdir(\".git\"):\n60\t        GIT_REVISION = git_version()\n61\t        ISRELEASED = False\n62\t    else:\n63\t        GIT_REVISION = \"RELEASE\"\n64\t        ISRELEASED = True\n65\t\n66\t    FULL_VERSION += \".dev-\" + GIT_REVISION\n67\t    text = cnt % {\n68\t        \"version\": VERSION,\n69\t        \"full_version\": FULL_VERSION,\n70\t        \"git_revision\": GIT_REVISION,\n71\t        \"isrelease\": str(ISRELEASED),\n72\t    }\n73\t    write_text(filename, text)\n74\t\n75\t\n76\there = os.path.abspath(os.path.dirname(__file__))\n77\twith open(os.path.join(here, \"README.md\"), encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n78\t    long_description = f.read()\n79\t\n80\twrite_version_py()\n81\tsetup(\n82\t    name=\"ILAMB\",\n83\t    version=VERSION,\n84\t    description=\"The International Land Model Benchmarking Package\",\n85\t    long_description=long_description,\n86\t    url=\"https://github.com/rubisco-sfa/ILAMB.git\",\n87\t    author=\"Nathan Collier\",\n88\t    author_email=\"nathaniel.collier@gmail.com\",\n89\t    license=\"BSD-3-Clause\",\n90\t    classifiers=[\n91\t        \"Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable\",\n92\t        \"Intended Audience :: Science/Research\",\n93\t        \"Topic :: Scientific/Engineering\",\n94\t        \"License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License\",\n95\t        \"Operating System :: MacOS\",\n96\t        \"Operating System :: POSIX\",\n97\t        \"Operating System :: POSIX :: Linux\",\n98\t        \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3\",\n99\t    ],\n100\t    keywords=[\n101\t        \"benchmarking\",\n102\t        \"earth system modeling\",\n103\t        \"climate modeling\",\n104\t        \"model intercomparison\",\n105\t    ],\n106\t    packages=[\"ILAMB\"],\n107\t    package_dir={\"\": \"src\"},\n108\t    package_data={\"ILAMB\": [\"data/*.cfg\", \"data/*.parquet\"]},\n109\t    scripts=[\"bin/ilamb-run\", \"bin/ilamb-fetch\", \"bin/ilamb-mean\", \"bin/ilamb-setup\"],\n110\t    zip_safe=False,\n111\t    install_requires=[\n112\t        \"numpy\",\n113\t        \"pandas\",\n114\t        \"matplotlib\",\n115\t        \"cartopy\",\n116\t        \"netCDF4\",\n117\t        \"cf-units\",\n118\t        \"sympy\",\n119\t        \"mpi4py\",\n120\t        \"scipy\",\n121\t        \"cftime\",\n122\t        \"tqdm\",\n123\t        \"pyarrow\",\n124\t        \"pyyaml\",\n125\t        \"requests\",\n126\t    ],\n127\t    extras_require={\n128\t        \"watershed\": [\"contextily\", \"geopandas\", \"dataretrieval\", \"pynhd\"],\n129\t    },\n130\t)\n131\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8f03c8eb-29e8-40b3-9ecc-11dd41b1ad27","uuid":"ab6b82f5-5f37-4f6e-b1b8-299c89b0a1e1","timestamp":"2026-04-09T00:42:07.472Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/setup.py","content":"#!/usr/bin/env python\nimport os\nimport subprocess\nfrom codecs import open\n\nfrom setuptools import setup\n\nVERSION = \"2.7.3\"\n\n\ndef git_version():\n    \"\"\"\n    Return the sha1 of local git HEAD as a string.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def _minimal_ext_cmd(cmd):\n        # construct minimal environment\n        env = {}\n        for k in [\"SYSTEMROOT\", \"PATH\", \"PYTHONPATH\"]:\n            v = os.environ.get(k)\n            if v is not None:\n                env[k] = v\n        # LANGUAGE is used on win32\n        env[\"LANGUAGE\"] = \"C\"\n        env[\"LANG\"] = \"C\"\n        env[\"LC_ALL\"] = \"C\"\n        out = subprocess.Popen(cmd, stdout=subprocess.PIPE, env=env).communicate()[0]\n        return out\n\n    try:\n        out = _minimal_ext_cmd([\"git\", \"rev-parse\", \"HEAD\"])\n        git_revision = out.strip().decode(\"ascii\")\n    except OSError:\n        git_revision = \"unknown-git\"\n    return git_revision[:7]\n\n\ndef write_text(filename, text):\n    try:\n        with open(filename, \"w\") as a:\n            a.write(text)\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(e)\n\n\ndef write_version_py(filename=os.path.join(\"src/ILAMB\", \"generated_version.py\")):\n    cnt = \"\"\"\n# THIS FILE IS GENERATED FROM ILAMB SETUP.PY\nshort_version = '%(version)s'\nversion = '%(version)s'\ngit_revision = '%(git_revision)s'\nfull_version = '%(version)s (%%(git_revision)s)' %% {\n    'git_revision': git_revision}\nrelease = %(isrelease)s\nif not release:\n    version = full_version\n\"\"\"\n    FULL_VERSION = VERSION\n    if os.path.isdir(\".git\"):\n        GIT_REVISION = git_version()\n        ISRELEASED = False\n    else:\n        GIT_REVISION = \"RELEASE\"\n        ISRELEASED = True\n\n    FULL_VERSION += \".dev-\" + GIT_REVISION\n    text = cnt % {\n        \"version\": VERSION,\n        \"full_version\": FULL_VERSION,\n        \"git_revision\": GIT_REVISION,\n        \"isrelease\": str(ISRELEASED),\n    }\n    write_text(filename, text)\n\n\nhere = os.path.abspath(os.path.dirname(__file__))\nwith open(os.path.join(here, \"README.md\"), encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n    long_description = f.read()\n\nwrite_version_py()\nsetup(\n    name=\"ILAMB\",\n    version=VERSION,\n    description=\"The International Land Model Benchmarking Package\",\n    long_description=long_description,\n    url=\"https://github.com/rubisco-sfa/ILAMB.git\",\n    author=\"Nathan Collier\",\n    author_email=\"nathaniel.collier@gmail.com\",\n    license=\"BSD-3-Clause\",\n    classifiers=[\n        \"Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable\",\n        \"Intended Audience :: Science/Research\",\n        \"Topic :: Scientific/Engineering\",\n        \"License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License\",\n        \"Operating System :: MacOS\",\n        \"Operating System :: POSIX\",\n        \"Operating System :: POSIX :: Linux\",\n        \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3\",\n    ],\n    keywords=[\n        \"benchmarking\",\n        \"earth system modeling\",\n        \"climate modeling\",\n        \"model intercomparison\",\n    ],\n    packages=[\"ILAMB\"],\n    package_dir={\"\": \"src\"},\n    package_data={\"ILAMB\": [\"data/*.cfg\", \"data/*.parquet\"]},\n    scripts=[\"bin/ilamb-run\", \"bin/ilamb-fetch\", \"bin/ilamb-mean\", \"bin/ilamb-setup\"],\n    zip_safe=False,\n    install_requires=[\n        \"numpy\",\n        \"pandas\",\n        \"matplotlib\",\n        \"cartopy\",\n        \"netCDF4\",\n        \"cf-units\",\n        \"sympy\",\n        \"mpi4py\",\n        \"scipy\",\n        \"cftime\",\n        \"tqdm\",\n        \"pyarrow\",\n        \"pyyaml\",\n        \"requests\",\n    ],\n    extras_require={\n        \"watershed\": [\"contextily\", \"geopandas\", \"dataretrieval\", \"pynhd\"],\n    },\n)\n","numLines":131,"startLine":1,"totalLines":131}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_2cd2d8e6985b40eda50dae02","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# This file creates an environment suitable for installing ILAMB. Use\n2\t# this file if you are running ILAMB on your personal machine or small\n3\t# cluster where you do not need to submit jobs into a queue to run.\n4\tname: ilamb\n5\tchannels:\n6\t  - conda-forge\n7\t  - defaults\n8\tdependencies:\n9\t  - python>=3.9\n10\t  - numpy\n11\t  - pandas\n12\t  - matplotlib\n13\t  - cartopy\n14\t  - netCDF4\n15\t  - cf-units\n16\t  - sympy\n17\t  - mpi4py\n18\t  - scipy\n19\t  - cftime\n20\t  - tqdm\n21\t  - pyarrow\n22\t  - pyyaml\n23\t  - requests\n24\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8f03c8eb-29e8-40b3-9ecc-11dd41b1ad27","uuid":"d3739d27-7607-48ce-8bf5-1d5a57a7331b","timestamp":"2026-04-09T00:42:07.473Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/ilamb.yml","content":"# This file creates an environment suitable for installing ILAMB. Use\n# this file if you are running ILAMB on your personal machine or small\n# cluster where you do not need to submit jobs into a queue to run.\nname: ilamb\nchannels:\n  - conda-forge\n  - defaults\ndependencies:\n  - python>=3.9\n  - numpy\n  - pandas\n  - matplotlib\n  - cartopy\n  - netCDF4\n  - cf-units\n  - sympy\n  - mpi4py\n  - scipy\n  - cftime\n  - tqdm\n  - pyarrow\n  - pyyaml\n  - requests\n","numLines":24,"startLine":1,"totalLines":24}}}
